Farewell, thou child of my right hand, and joy;  
How swiftly flown the days of golden light,  
Your laughter ringing, bright without alloy,  
Now echoes softly through the silent night.  

Your tiny fingers clung to dreams and days,  
Each moment kindled wonder in my chest;  
Now memory’s gentle hand alone conveys  
The warmth you left, the hope, the silent rest.  

Farewell, sweet soul, as stars ascend above;  
You dwell in peace, forever held by love.
